    "## 1.1 What is TensorFlow?\n",
    "\n",
    "TensorFlow is an end-to-end machine learning framework designed to build and deploy deep learning models efficiently. It converts neural network computations into optimized computational graphs that can run on GPUs and TPUs.\n",
    "\n",
    "Beyond model training, TensorFlow also provides tools for production-grade workflows, monitoring, and serving models in real-world systems.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Figure 1.1 — Components of TensorFlow**\n",
   ![Figure 1.1](figure/fig/figure1.1.png)
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1.2 GPU vs CPU\n",
    "\n",
    "Deep learning workloads rely heavily on operations like matrix multiplication. GPUs excel at performing these operations in parallel, massively accelerating training.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **GPU** → ideal for training deep networks (CNNs, RNNs, Transformers)\n",
    "- **CPU** → suitable for lighter tasks such as preprocessing or small models\n",
    "\n",
    "**Figure 1.2 — CPU vs GPU Differences**\n",
    "![Figure 1.2](./fig/figure1.2.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1.3 When and When Not to Use TensorFlow\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Use TensorFlow when:**\n",
    "- Building deep learning models\n",
    "- Training on large datasets\n",
    "- Leveraging multi-GPU/TPU acceleration\n",
    "- Deploying ML workflows with TensorFlow Extended (TFX)\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Avoid TensorFlow when:**\n",
    "- Working with very small structured datasets\n",
    "- Building traditional ML models requiring minimal computation\n",
    "- Handling heavy NLP preprocessing pipelines\n",
    "\n",
    "**Figure 1.3 — ML Workflow Example**\n",
    "![Figure 1.3](./fig/figure1.3.png)"
   ]
  },
